The Ondo State Police Command on Sunday arrested a prophet for stage managing miracles in order to engage in s*x with women looking for the fruit of the womb. P.M.Express reports as was disclosed by the Police Public Relations Officer in the state, Mr. Femi Joseph, who confirmed that the suspect confessed to the crime during interrogation. The Police said the suspect was arrested in Igbokoda, the headquarters of the Ilaje Local Government Area of the state last month. According to the Police, the suspect had allegedly been staging fake miracles to deceive unsuspecting members of the public. The PPRO, Mr. Joseph said, “One Sunday Ayetare, 35, a native of Itepe Okitipupa, was arrested on a crusade ground of a white garment church in Igbokoda for offences of attempted rape and sexual harassment”. “On interrogation, the suspect also confessed to be a fake prophet, who had been deceiving people by staging fake miracles. He stated further that he deceived his latest victim, who was looking unto God for a child, by telling her that he could make her pregnant.” “He added that in the process, he sexually harassed the woman and attempted to r*pe her. “It was, however, established that the suspect was never a Policeman, but an impostor and a serial fraudster.” Joseph added that the Command would not relent in its efforts to flush out criminals from the state, stating that the suspect will be charged to Court after the conclusion of investigation. Source